<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n37009f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n37" href="#n37009f">N37 (VI.B.28A)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n37all.htm#n37009f"> 9(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 142 &ldquo;worked the press&rdquo;</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[<font size="-1">THE SWEDISH NIGHTINGALE</font> [Jenny Lind]</font>]: Barnum hired <font color="green">[an English newspaper writer]</font> to write articles <font color="green">[about Jenny Lind]</font> of one or two newspaper columns once or twice each week, as long as his ingenuity and Barnum&apos;s suggestions held out. &hellip; The articles were dated &ldquo;London&rdquo; and appeared as special correspondence from that city. Barnum told a reporter for the <i>Chicago Tribune</i> in June, 1890, &ldquo;I suppose that was the first attempt in this country to &lsquo;<mark>work the press</mark>&rsquo;. I am free to confess that it couldn&apos;t be done now. Besides, it is not necessary.&rdquo; <small> M.R. Werner, <a name="MRWP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MRWP"><cite title="source">P.T. Barnum</cite></a> (1923) 142</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
